message.text:
KANJI Quiz!
Do you know the meaning of the Kanji "休"？ Choose the answer!
1. man 2. same 3. breaktime
Having busy time at the beginning of the new school/business year?
Take a rest for relaxation sometimes!
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/School/　　
「休」の意味はどれ？新学期/新年度、息抜きもしつつがんばりましょう！

message.text:
"WA Project" - ASIA CENTER Initiated!
The Japan Foundation will boost exchanges with the Asian countries in the coming seven years leading up to the 2020 Olympics and Paralympics, held in Tokyo. We will COMMUNICATE, CONNECT and SHARE, COLLABORATE, and CREATE to enhance interactive exchange on an equal footing with our friends in Asia. 
http://jfac.jp/
アジアの絆を強くする。「文化のWAプロジェクト」-アジアセンター始動！
(c)Mariko Tagashira

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "SHI" SHI M BU N　　#nihongo
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！　「し」んぶん

Japanese newspapers are usually written vertically and the page layout is right-to-left, but webpage are written horizontally like English.The reading direction should be reversed!
日本語は縦書きと横書きがあって、読む方向も逆になります！
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_keyword.php?q=%E3%81%97%E3%82%93%E3%81%B6%E3%82%93&lang=en
